# Local Formidable client state, never shared across clones.
# Each Formidable user keeps their own ledger of "what did I last sync"
# at this path; committing it would cause one user's local state to
# silently overwrite another's on the next pull.
.formidable/sync.json

# Log files. Formidable and the tooling around it write runtime logs
# alongside content; checking them in pollutes the team repo with
# per-user noise that's only ever interesting on the machine that
# produced it. Both patterns so old git versions that don't recurse
# `*.log` into subdirectories still ignore nested `<dir>/foo.log`.
*.log
**/*.log
